CNMV approves the public exclusion of Paternina presented by the investment company Mer
The National Stock Exchange Commission (CNMV) approved the public exclusion invitation for Federico Paternina submitted by the investment company Mer on 9 October.
The supervisory authority stated that it approved this invitation to tender after it had been proven that the conditions of the laws were complied with and that the contents of the explanatory leaflet submitted, after the amendments of last 2 December, could be considered "sufficient".
CNMV has also announced that this offer aims at acquiring 550.008 shares of Federico Paternina at the price of 7.65 euros per share, which in turn represents 8.95 % of the company's capital, consisting of 6,142,786 euros in shares admitted to the Madrid and Bilbao stock exchanges.
In addition, it has been notified that 5.592.778 million shares have been fixed which can in no way be transferred until the end of the tender and whose price has been fixed by Federico Paternina in accordance with the laws.
New vehicle assessment programmes
In these days of storms and accidents not only the car workshops deserve
Each day, thousands of vehicles involved in an accident are towed into the workshops where an expert has to assess the damage caused and the costs of repair.
No accident is equal and the calculation of costs for parts and working hours can be a long and complicated task.
The calculation of repair costs of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros by hand, including parts and working hours, may take up to two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the support of the latest computer tools, it is a matter of minutes
That is why almost 100 % of the experts use this type of system.
The service providers and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs shall collect the information they receive from the manufacturers to process them afterwards and offer them to their customers in the form of a useful program.
In Spain, Audatex, part of the American group Solera, is the market leader; 80% of all the opinions are produced with their products.
The two other companies competing in the tool market for evaluation and preparation of a report are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by the manufacturers is anything but simple.
According to Eduardo Vel√°zquez, sales manager of Audatex, 63 producers and importers are working together, each of whom provides the information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is growing, up to the point that over the last five years more versions, variants and motorizations have come on the market than in the whole fifteen years before.
As soon as a new car enters the market, work starts for the companies.
It is a laborious task, because every single one of the thousand parts of the vehicle must be catabolized and its price entered.
In addition, each model creates an "intelligent" graphic image on which you can "click" on different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a much-sold model, work can be completed in one week if the procedure proceeds quickly.
If this is a less common car, it may take up to three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information at 99.2% of the cars sold in Spain.
Among the more exclusive models, they have information about the Porsche models, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the road-driven vehicle park, it is above 99%.
Audatex has eight centres distributed worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) for the execution of the documentation and the production of databases and each of them has specialized in certain brands.
Its national headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanical experts) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex invests 90 million euros annually in the development of these databases.
Every month they record 2.5 million data and their customers receive updates every second day.
The development of this vast flow of information enables companies to use it in different ways and thus offer different products.
The most common use is the use of repairs and repairs, but there are also tools for the management of scrap parts depending on the country or for the calculation of the file or residual value of a car.
The only company that informs of the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex offers this offer not in Spain, but in the United States.
The transparency of the products offered by Audatex makes it easy to get an overview of the type of support given to industry experts.
This company offers ten different tools, the star of the products AudaPlus, a standard solution for assessing accidents for the experts.
It includes vehicles, motorcycles and light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it includes the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the paint prices.
This tool is paid according to the purpose of use, i.e. for each opinion.
It will be most expensive for customers who rarely use it up to ten times a month, namely 5,75 euros per month.
On the other hand, every insurance company that produces thousands of opinions negotiates the price with Audatex.
With other products, such as AudaVIN, you can fully identify a vehicle and the equipment with which it ran from the mounting belt using the chassis number alone.
AudaGlass deals with the vehicle discs, and AudaSubastas is an Internet service open to the specialist market, which can be used for vehicles that have been declared total damage.
